WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.810 --> 00:00:06.914
♪ Carry on. my wayward son ♪

2
00:00:06.916 --> 00:00:12.219
♪ there'll be peace
when you are done ♪

3
00:00:12.954 --> 00:00:18.058
♪ lay your weary head to rest ♪

4
00:00:18.060 --> 00:00:22.930
♪ Don't you cry no more ♪

5
00:00:24.566 --> 00:00:26.934
I will save my brother
or die trying.

6
00:00:26.936 --> 00:00:28.168
It's the Mark of Cain.

7
00:00:28.170 --> 00:00:29.703
It's just a curse.
It can be removed.

8
00:00:29.705 --> 00:00:31.839
You're their bitch.
Get out.

9
00:00:31.841 --> 00:00:33.407
"The Book of the Damned"
is a spell book

10
00:00:33.409 --> 00:00:35.576
for creating or undoing

11
00:00:35.578 --> 00:00:37.444
any kind of damnation
there is.

12
00:00:37.446 --> 00:00:38.679
I think this is in code.

13
00:00:38.681 --> 00:00:40.681
Bring me Nadya's codex.

14
00:00:40.683 --> 00:00:42.783
and I'll break this text
right open.

15
00:00:42.785 --> 00:00:46.653
♪ Once I rose above the noise
and confusion ♪

16
00:00:46.655 --> 00:00:50.034
♪ just to get a glimpse
beyond this illusion ♪

17
00:00:50.058 --> 00:00:51.192
Dean is not getting
any better.

18
00:00:51.193 --> 00:00:53.804
if we don't get the mark off
his arm. it's gonna eat him up.

19
00:00:53.805 --> 00:00:55.429
♪ I was soaring ever higher ♪

20
00:00:55.430 --> 00:00:57.564
♪ But I flew too high ♪

21
00:00:57.566 --> 00:00:59.566
My grace.
it's been restored.

22
00:00:59.568 --> 00:01:02.836
♪ Though my eyes could see
I still was a blind man ♪

23
00:01:02.838 --> 00:01:06.338
Find me a cure for my brother.
Then I'll kill Crowley.

24
00:01:06.339 --> 00:01:07.073
♪ I still was a mad man ♪
Thank you. Sam...

25
00:01:07.076 --> 00:01:09.843
♪ I hear the voices when I'm dreaming ♪
...For reminding me who I really am.

26
00:01:09.845 --> 00:01:12.179
There must be <i>something</i>
that I don't know about her.

27
00:01:12.181 --> 00:01:14.314
something I could hold over her
as a bargaining chip.

28
00:01:14.316 --> 00:01:18.318
♪ Carry on. my wayward son ♪
She's cracked the code.

29
00:01:18.320 --> 00:01:20.087
♪ There'll be peace
when you are done ♪

30
00:01:20.089 --> 00:01:21.688
Charlie?

31
00:01:22.423 --> 00:01:23.724
♪ Lay your weary head to rest ♪

32
00:01:23.726 --> 00:01:25.826
I don't want
to have to hurt you.

33
00:01:25.828 --> 00:01:28.829
♪ don't you cry no more ♪
I don't think that's gonna be a problem.

34
00:01:53.621 --> 00:01:55.055
Anything?

35
00:01:56.691 --> 00:01:58.659
12 voicemails.

36
00:01:58.661 --> 00:02:02.863
LoJack on the Impala
has clearly been disabled.

37
00:02:02.865 --> 00:02:05.065
So a big heaping scoop
of nothing.

38
00:02:05.067 --> 00:02:09.436
We need Rowena to hold up
her end of the bargain -- now.

39
00:02:11.005 --> 00:02:13.373
What?

40
00:02:13.375 --> 00:02:14.775
Nothing.

41
00:02:14.777 --> 00:02:16.577
It's -- it's just
if she removes the Mark

42
00:02:16.579 --> 00:02:19.413
using
"The Book of the Damned"...

43
00:02:19.415 --> 00:02:20.881
What of the consequences?

44
00:02:20.883 --> 00:02:22.382
Which are what?

45
00:02:22.384 --> 00:02:23.584
Dean said --

46
00:02:23.586 --> 00:02:24.751
Dean guessed!

47
00:02:29.758 --> 00:02:31.325
Guess.

48
00:02:31.327 --> 00:02:32.859
What are we
supposed to do. huh?

49
00:02:34.062 --> 00:02:35.362
Just sit on our asses.
do nothing?

50
00:02:35.364 --> 00:02:37.064
No. We find Dean.

51
00:02:37.066 --> 00:02:38.398
And then what?!

52
00:02:38.400 --> 00:02:41.635
The only thing that stopped
Cain was death.

53
00:02:41.637 --> 00:02:43.604
Do you want to kill Dean?
Because I don't.

54
00:02:43.606 --> 00:02:44.838
And the only way I know

55
00:02:44.840 --> 00:02:46.673
how to save my brother
is to cure the Mark.

56
00:02:46.675 --> 00:02:48.575
And. yes. I know
there will be consequences.

57
00:02:48.577 --> 00:02:50.711
but not you. not Dean --

58
00:02:50.713 --> 00:02:53.247
not anybody can tell me
what those consequences are.

59
00:02:53.249 --> 00:02:56.883
So I'm not gonna let my brother
d-destroy himself on a guess.

60
00:03:01.323 --> 00:03:05.025
We save Dean.

61
00:03:30.218 --> 00:03:31.885
Ahh.

62
00:03:38.260 --> 00:03:40.827
I'm good.

63
00:03:42.631 --> 00:03:44.398
I'm good.

64
00:03:47.869 --> 00:03:51.869
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Supernatural 10x23 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Brother's Keeper</font>
Original Air Date on May 20. 2015

65
00:03:51.893 --> 00:03:56.593
== sync. corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

66
00:04:03.951 --> 00:04:05.585
Rose McKinley.

67
00:04:05.587 --> 00:04:08.422
Raised up
about three miles from here.

68
00:04:08.424 --> 00:04:11.258
Nice parents.
God-fearin' folk.

69
00:04:11.260 --> 00:04:13.460
Well. they let her leave the
house looking like a whore.

70
00:04:14.195 --> 00:04:15.629
Whoa.

71
00:04:16.664 --> 00:04:18.165
Why don't you tell me
what you really think. Agent?

72
00:04:18.167 --> 00:04:20.067
Oh. I'm sorry. Sheriff.
My bad.

73
00:04:20.069 --> 00:04:23.470
Let me tell you
how we work out here. son.

74
00:04:23.472 --> 00:04:26.073
That right there could be
the whore of Babylon --

75
00:04:26.075 --> 00:04:27.941
wouldn't make
no difference at all.

76
00:04:27.943 --> 00:04:30.243
'Cause all I see is
somebody's little girl.

77
00:04:30.245 --> 00:04:33.046
And I feel like a real jerk
suggesting otherwise. Sheriff.

78
00:04:33.048 --> 00:04:35.282
My apologies.

79
00:04:36.651 --> 00:04:38.952
Good luck crackin' the case
with your eyes shut.

80
00:04:40.355 --> 00:04:42.255
You worked some pretty
dark stuff in your day.

81
00:04:42.257 --> 00:04:43.423
haven't you. Agent?

82
00:04:43.425 --> 00:04:46.860
Must've left
quite a mark.

83
00:04:46.862 --> 00:04:48.495
Oh. you have no idea.

84
00:04:49.798 --> 00:04:51.298
Your partner's
a piece of work. Agent.

85
00:04:51.300 --> 00:04:53.166
Yeah. ain't he. though?

86
00:04:53.168 --> 00:04:55.035
Dean-o!

87
00:04:55.037 --> 00:04:56.770
Welcome to the party.

88
00:04:56.772 --> 00:04:58.271
The hell you doing here.
Rudy?

89
00:04:58.273 --> 00:05:00.374
Ah. you know. just a thing
I got for dead girls.

90
00:05:03.411 --> 00:05:05.912
Just -- just workin'
a gang of fang. you know?

91
00:05:05.914 --> 00:05:07.114
Just like you.

92
00:05:07.116 --> 00:05:08.615
Yeah.
not today you're not.

93
00:05:08.617 --> 00:05:10.517
I'm gonna need you
to take a walk on this one.

94
00:05:10.519 --> 00:05:13.420
Uh. okay. except. uh --
except I called you.

95
00:05:13.422 --> 00:05:15.822
so. uh. if anybody's walking.
it's --

96
00:05:15.824 --> 00:05:19.593
Oh. you called me?
No. no. You begged me.

97
00:05:19.595 --> 00:05:22.829
Just like Tuscaloosa.
just like Old Lyme.

98
00:05:22.831 --> 00:05:24.965
we both know you're playing
dress-up out here.

99
00:05:24.967 --> 00:05:27.033
and it's just a matter of time
before you get yourself killed.

100
00:05:27.035 --> 00:05:28.435
So why don't you
take that walk

101
00:05:28.437 --> 00:05:30.170
and let the real hunters
do the work?

102
00:05:30.172 --> 00:05:32.973
Agents!
New deal.

103
00:05:32.975 --> 00:05:35.909
Rose wasn't alone
when she disappeared.

104
00:05:35.911 --> 00:05:38.612
Friend named Crystal Thorrson
was with her.

105
00:05:38.614 --> 00:05:40.180
and Crystal is still AWOL.

106
00:05:40.182 --> 00:05:42.883
I'm heading over
to interview the parents.

107
00:05:42.885 --> 00:05:45.919
How about we agree
you boys sit this one out?

108
00:05:47.488 --> 00:05:49.489
You know something?

109
00:05:49.491 --> 00:05:52.859
Life's too short...
Partner.

110
00:05:52.861 --> 00:05:55.228
You know. I don't know what
crawled up your ass today.

111
00:05:55.230 --> 00:05:56.730
but frankly.
I don't care.

112
00:05:59.767 --> 00:06:01.535
Regards to your brother.

113
00:06:17.285 --> 00:06:19.886
Hello. boys.

114
00:06:19.888 --> 00:06:22.889
Just in time for tea --
u-unless something on your mind?

115
00:06:22.891 --> 00:06:24.357
Five things. actually.

116
00:06:25.828 --> 00:06:28.862
Hollow tips filled
with witch-killing brew.

117
00:06:28.864 --> 00:06:31.665
How exciting for you.

118
00:06:31.667 --> 00:06:35.202
Your NRA will be beside
themselves with pride.

119
00:06:35.204 --> 00:06:37.070
No more games. Rowena.

120
00:06:37.072 --> 00:06:39.406
Do the spell now.

121
00:06:39.408 --> 00:06:42.909
Or what exactly?

122
00:06:42.911 --> 00:06:44.544
Come on. Samuel!

123
00:06:44.546 --> 00:06:46.980
You and I both know
that's nothing but a bluff.

124
00:06:46.982 --> 00:06:49.082
Charlie may have
cracked the codex.

125
00:06:49.084 --> 00:06:50.884
but who's going to read it
if I'm gone?

126
00:06:50.886 --> 00:06:52.552
Not to mention
handling the ingredients.

127
00:06:52.554 --> 00:06:54.087
getting the measurements
just right --

128
00:06:54.089 --> 00:06:56.122
unless. of course.
either of you

129
00:06:56.124 --> 00:06:59.259
have spent years of your life
studying with the greats.

130
00:06:59.261 --> 00:07:01.895
mastering the intricacies
of high witchcraft?

131
00:07:01.897 --> 00:07:05.599
But forgive me.
Maybe you have.

132
00:07:09.403 --> 00:07:10.804
I know you're upset.

133
00:07:10.806 --> 00:07:12.072
We all are.

134
00:07:12.074 --> 00:07:15.709
Poor Dean.

135
00:07:15.711 --> 00:07:19.546
Let's just have
a nice wee cup of tea...

136
00:07:19.548 --> 00:07:21.314
and negotiate.

137
00:07:25.521 --> 00:07:26.653
What do you want?

138
00:07:26.655 --> 00:07:27.854
Oh. well.

139
00:07:27.856 --> 00:07:29.956
we know what I wanted.

140
00:07:29.958 --> 00:07:32.459
Soiled the sheets
on that one. didn't we?

141
00:07:32.461 --> 00:07:34.494
Let's talk about
what I'll take --

142
00:07:34.496 --> 00:07:37.964
my freedom guaranteed

143
00:07:37.966 --> 00:07:39.332
and the codex.

144
00:07:41.035 --> 00:07:42.335
Sam. you can't be --

145
00:07:42.337 --> 00:07:43.770
Do you know which spell?

146
00:07:46.240 --> 00:07:48.775
I do.

147
00:07:48.777 --> 00:07:50.644
Sam.

148
00:07:50.646 --> 00:07:53.647
This is a mistake.

149
00:07:55.616 --> 00:07:59.319
Rose and Crystal
were friends since...

150
00:07:59.321 --> 00:08:01.688
forever it seems.

151
00:08:03.224 --> 00:08:06.326
Uh. you think that Crystal
could still be in danger?

152
00:08:06.328 --> 00:08:08.662
We do. Mrs. McKinley. and
the fastest way to find Crystal

153
00:08:08.664 --> 00:08:10.330
is to find out
who did this to Rose.

154
00:08:10.332 --> 00:08:14.100
Did you notice any change
in her behavior recently --

155
00:08:14.102 --> 00:08:18.204
uh. new friends.
a new boyfriend. maybe a crush?

156
00:08:18.206 --> 00:08:22.576
Rose was...a shy girl.

157
00:08:25.446 --> 00:08:29.449
But...you think she might know
who did this to her?

158
00:08:29.451 --> 00:08:31.818
In Rose's case.
she not only knew the person.

159
00:08:31.820 --> 00:08:34.154
but. uh. she was trying
to have intercourse with them.

160
00:08:34.156 --> 00:08:37.123
So I'm just trying to figure out
whether it was a boyfriend

161
00:08:37.125 --> 00:08:40.393
or whether it was just
some random roll in the hay.

162
00:08:40.861 --> 00:08:42.329
No.

163
00:08:42.331 --> 00:08:46.433
Uh. there were no relations
that we're aware of.

164
00:08:46.435 --> 00:08:49.769
No relations at all.
What the hell is this. Agent?

165
00:08:49.771 --> 00:08:51.237
I'm just doing my job.
Mr. McKinley.

166
00:08:51.239 --> 00:08:53.707
By suggesting
my daughter was a slut?

167
00:08:53.709 --> 00:08:55.575
I'll admit
that thought crossed my mind.

168
00:08:57.011 --> 00:08:58.678
Then I came here.
and I smelled the deceit

169
00:08:58.680 --> 00:09:00.814
and the beatings and the shame
that pervade this home.

170
00:09:00.816 --> 00:09:02.983
And you know what?
I don't blame Rose anymore.

171
00:09:02.985 --> 00:09:05.385
You shut your face right now.
No wonder she put on that skank outfit

172
00:09:05.387 --> 00:09:08.121
and went out there
looking for validation.

173
00:09:08.123 --> 00:09:09.856
right into the arms
of the monster that killed her.

174
00:09:09.858 --> 00:09:11.625
Joe. who did this?

175
00:09:11.627 --> 00:09:13.760
No! Joe!

176
00:09:13.762 --> 00:09:15.762
Who did this?
Stop!

177
00:09:15.764 --> 00:09:17.197
Joe.

178
00:09:18.099 --> 00:09:19.833
Who did this?

179
00:09:27.009 --> 00:09:29.676
I don't know.

180
00:09:31.545 --> 00:09:34.681
I don't know!

181
00:09:52.668 --> 00:09:54.300
Whoa.
What?

182
00:09:54.302 --> 00:09:57.337
Crystal.
she's still...

183
00:09:57.339 --> 00:09:59.606
Why?

184
00:10:01.743 --> 00:10:03.977
There were these guys
living out by Cross Creek.

185
00:10:03.979 --> 00:10:06.780
said they were
rehabbing a cabin out there.

186
00:10:06.782 --> 00:10:08.348
Mostly.
I think they just wanted

187
00:10:08.350 --> 00:10:10.216
a place
to drink and meet girls.

188
00:10:10.218 --> 00:10:12.452
And Crystal and your sister
knew these guys?

189
00:10:14.088 --> 00:10:15.889
But you couldn't be bothered
to tell the cops that

190
00:10:15.891 --> 00:10:17.223
when your sister
turned up dead?

191
00:10:17.225 --> 00:10:18.725
I was sort of the one

192
00:10:18.727 --> 00:10:20.527
who brought them out there
in the first place.

193
00:10:22.763 --> 00:10:30.770
<i>"Sumsu mimma ezebu</i>
<i>ilu ma ikkibu Lu."</i>

194
00:10:30.772 --> 00:10:36.509
"S-something made by God.
but forbidden to man."

195
00:10:36.511 --> 00:10:38.912
Forbidden?

196
00:10:38.914 --> 00:10:41.181
The forbidden fruit?

197
00:10:43.118 --> 00:10:44.718
No.

198
00:10:47.922 --> 00:10:52.158
The actual apple
is the first ingredient?

199
00:10:52.160 --> 00:10:54.427
<i>"Sumsu mimma ezebu Lu."</i>

200
00:10:54.429 --> 00:10:56.129
da-da. da-da. da-da.
Okay. uh. what's next?

201
00:10:56.131 --> 00:11:01.000
"Something made by man.
but forbidden by God."

202
00:11:01.002 --> 00:11:04.437
Okay. well. God forbade
false idols. right?

203
00:11:04.439 --> 00:11:06.372
The Golden Calf.

204
00:11:07.341 --> 00:11:09.242
Wasn't that destroyed?

205
00:11:10.311 --> 00:11:12.612
<i>"Sumsu mimma sen arramu."</i>

206
00:11:12.614 --> 00:11:14.714
Great.

207
00:11:14.716 --> 00:11:16.382
What's
the third ingredient?

208
00:11:20.254 --> 00:11:22.088
Oh.

209
00:11:22.090 --> 00:11:23.156
What?

210
00:11:24.325 --> 00:11:26.993
The third ingredient.
it's impossible.

211
00:11:26.995 --> 00:11:28.595
What is it?

212
00:11:28.597 --> 00:11:33.199
Loosely translated --
my heart.

213
00:11:33.201 --> 00:11:35.368
It's not impossible
at all.

214
00:11:35.370 --> 00:11:37.570
Not my literal heart.
feathers.

215
00:11:37.572 --> 00:11:40.406
Something I love. the spell
calls for me to kill it.

216
00:11:40.408 --> 00:11:42.509
A sacrifice.
Precisely.

217
00:11:42.511 --> 00:11:44.210
The book will grant
freedom from the curse.

218
00:11:44.212 --> 00:11:46.446
but it wants something in return.
Well. then give it.

219
00:11:46.448 --> 00:11:48.414
Bring me something I love.
I'll kill it.

220
00:11:48.416 --> 00:11:50.717
I want my freedom too much
to make a fuss over that.

221
00:11:50.719 --> 00:11:52.986
The -- the problem is.
I don't love anything.

222
00:11:52.988 --> 00:11:54.788
What about Crowley?

223
00:11:54.790 --> 00:11:57.557
Happy to kill him.
Let's not call it love.

224
00:11:57.559 --> 00:11:59.125
I don't believe you.

225
00:12:00.094 --> 00:12:01.995
Everyone loves something.

226
00:12:03.931 --> 00:12:06.132
Oskar!

227
00:12:06.134 --> 00:12:08.201
Oskar!

228
00:12:09.203 --> 00:12:12.338
<i>Czas Na kolacje!</i>

229
00:12:15.142 --> 00:12:18.244
Polish boy. Oskar.

230
00:12:18.246 --> 00:12:21.147
I'm sorry. Oskar?

231
00:12:21.149 --> 00:12:23.216
You saw Oskar?

232
00:12:23.218 --> 00:12:25.451
Who is he?
Who was he?

233
00:12:25.453 --> 00:12:27.954
Uh. a peasant boy -- his family
helped me through some difficulties.

234
00:12:27.956 --> 00:12:29.656
300 years ago.

235
00:12:33.495 --> 00:12:34.928
Rudy. What's up?

236
00:12:34.930 --> 00:12:37.030
Wish I could say
it was good news. Sam.

237
00:12:37.032 --> 00:12:38.565
I just bumped into Dean

238
00:12:38.567 --> 00:12:41.234
working a fangbanger
case in Superior.

239
00:12:41.236 --> 00:12:44.337
Dean's in Nebraska.
w-working a case?

240
00:12:44.339 --> 00:12:46.706
Yeah. my case.

241
00:12:46.708 --> 00:12:48.708
And. uh...

242
00:12:48.710 --> 00:12:50.643
He's not playing well
with others.

243
00:12:50.645 --> 00:12:55.181
Yeah. Dean's not exactly
in the best place right now.

244
00:12:55.183 --> 00:12:56.749
You know what?
Do me a favor.

245
00:12:56.751 --> 00:12:58.451
Just text me the details.
would you?

246
00:12:58.453 --> 00:12:59.552
All right.
Whatever you need.

247
00:12:59.554 --> 00:13:01.120
Okay. Thanks.

248
00:13:04.491 --> 00:13:05.859
What's going on?

249
00:13:05.861 --> 00:13:08.361
Cass. take this.

250
00:13:08.363 --> 00:13:10.063
It's Dean's hair.
You need it for the spell.

251
00:13:10.065 --> 00:13:12.765
Cass. I need you
to do this for me.

252
00:13:12.767 --> 00:13:16.035
Make the spell happen
whatever it takes. please.

253
00:13:41.062 --> 00:13:43.796
Dean-o.
uh. this is Reggie.

254
00:13:43.798 --> 00:13:45.899
We're just gonna talk.
all right?

255
00:13:45.901 --> 00:13:48.301
And -- and come
to an understanding.

256
00:13:48.303 --> 00:13:50.236
Back your ass
out of the room. mister.

257
00:13:50.238 --> 00:13:51.671
and leave the blade.

258
00:13:52.606 --> 00:13:54.274
Yeah.

259
00:13:54.276 --> 00:13:55.508
No.

260
00:13:55.510 --> 00:13:56.609
Rudy. walk away.

261
00:13:56.611 --> 00:13:58.077
No. D-- no. d-Dean-o.

262
00:13:58.079 --> 00:13:59.512
just do
what he says. okay?

263
00:13:59.514 --> 00:14:00.613
He's not gonna kill you.

264
00:14:00.615 --> 00:14:02.081
You're his insurance.
all right?

265
00:14:02.083 --> 00:14:04.350
Now man the hell up
and walk away.

266
00:14:04.352 --> 00:14:05.852
Oh. I will kill him.
friend.

267
00:14:05.854 --> 00:14:07.220
You keep yappin'.
I will.

268
00:14:07.222 --> 00:14:08.721
Do it.
Dean!

269
00:14:08.723 --> 00:14:10.256
Back up.
Do it.

270
00:14:10.258 --> 00:14:11.991
D-don't test me.

271
00:14:11.993 --> 00:14:13.226
Dean. stop!

272
00:14:13.228 --> 00:14:14.894
You don't have
the guts.

273
00:14:28.009 --> 00:14:30.643
What did you do?!

274
00:14:32.179 --> 00:14:33.546
You're Crystal. right?

275
00:14:35.349 --> 00:14:37.684
Yeah. well...

276
00:14:37.686 --> 00:14:38.952
I just rescued you.

277
00:14:38.954 --> 00:14:41.154
He --
you could've talked.

278
00:14:41.156 --> 00:14:43.189
You just...

279
00:14:43.191 --> 00:14:44.624
You're welcome.

280
00:15:43.427 --> 00:15:46.195
He just let him die.

281
00:15:46.196 --> 00:15:48.896
He just let him die.

282
00:15:48.898 --> 00:15:51.432
Just let him die.

283
00:15:59.508 --> 00:16:01.542
Agent.

284
00:16:01.544 --> 00:16:04.912
Maybe you can tell me what in
the hell is going on here.

285
00:16:04.914 --> 00:16:07.482
The way the girl outside
tells it

286
00:16:07.484 --> 00:16:10.818
is one of your boys came
in hot. got his partner killed.

287
00:16:10.820 --> 00:16:12.420
then went
some kind of samurai

288
00:16:12.422 --> 00:16:14.389
on that son of a bitch
over there.

289
00:16:14.391 --> 00:16:16.457
I knew that boy...

290
00:16:34.677 --> 00:16:36.811
Who summons anymore?

291
00:16:36.813 --> 00:16:38.446
Couldn't you call?

292
00:16:38.448 --> 00:16:40.648
You're not
in my contacts list.

293
00:16:42.351 --> 00:16:43.584
What?

294
00:16:43.586 --> 00:16:45.887
I need your assistance

295
00:16:45.890 --> 00:16:47.956
to help cure Dean
of the Mark.

296
00:16:47.957 --> 00:16:50.958
What's the expression
I gave at the office?

297
00:16:50.960 --> 00:16:52.960
Maybe I'd feel
a little different

298
00:16:52.962 --> 00:16:55.830
if Sam Winchester hadn't
just tried to bloody kill me!

299
00:16:55.832 --> 00:17:00.601
I'm afraid "no" is not
an acceptable answer.

300
00:17:00.603 --> 00:17:01.803
Or what?

301
00:17:01.805 --> 00:17:03.905
Or...

302
00:17:03.907 --> 00:17:05.339
That's right.

303
00:17:05.341 --> 00:17:07.074
Burn those eyes blue.

304
00:17:07.076 --> 00:17:10.111
Spread those broken wings
and destroy me!

305
00:17:10.113 --> 00:17:14.315
Or...Do it my way.

306
00:17:14.317 --> 00:17:16.517
Right.

307
00:17:16.519 --> 00:17:18.019
Now beg.

308
00:17:20.456 --> 00:17:21.689
What?

309
00:17:21.691 --> 00:17:24.158
Blast me. or beg.

310
00:17:24.160 --> 00:17:25.827
Crowley.

311
00:17:25.829 --> 00:17:26.829
King!

312
00:17:28.163 --> 00:17:29.530
King.

313
00:17:31.633 --> 00:17:33.000
If you --
if you would --

314
00:17:33.002 --> 00:17:34.702
if you would be
so kind...

315
00:17:36.004 --> 00:17:38.239
The three ingredients
on this list.

316
00:17:40.142 --> 00:17:41.576
"Forbidden fruit."

317
00:17:41.578 --> 00:17:43.511
Well. for starters.

318
00:17:43.513 --> 00:17:46.113
it's a Quince. you dummy.
not an apple.

319
00:17:46.115 --> 00:17:47.615
No problem.

320
00:17:47.617 --> 00:17:50.685
"Golden Calf"...
Or what's left of it --

321
00:17:50.687 --> 00:17:52.119
check.

322
00:17:52.121 --> 00:17:54.155
"Something Rowena loves"?

323
00:17:54.157 --> 00:17:55.656
I would've thought
it would've been you. but...

324
00:17:55.658 --> 00:17:58.226
Spare me.
I've lived it.

325
00:18:05.768 --> 00:18:07.668
Well...

326
00:18:07.670 --> 00:18:09.170
I'm in.

327
00:18:33.363 --> 00:18:35.897
Dean. it's me.

328
00:19:31.553 --> 00:19:35.756
<i>Te nunc invoco. mortem.</i>

329
00:19:35.758 --> 00:19:38.092
<i>Te in mea potestate defixi.</i>

330
00:19:39.862 --> 00:19:45.132
<i>Nunc et in aeternum.</i>

331
00:19:52.240 --> 00:19:56.310
Don't tell me
that's queso.

332
00:19:57.346 --> 00:19:58.913
Yeah -- yes.

333
00:19:58.915 --> 00:20:05.086
Queso and. uh.
taquitos. tamales.

334
00:20:05.088 --> 00:20:08.322
Homemade
by yours truly.

335
00:20:08.324 --> 00:20:10.524
All with the bad fat.

336
00:20:12.061 --> 00:20:13.995
Consider it an offering.

337
00:20:13.997 --> 00:20:15.997
For?

338
00:20:15.999 --> 00:20:19.367
I want you to kill me.

339
00:20:25.376 --> 00:20:28.445
What I find
truly fascinating. Dean...

340
00:20:28.447 --> 00:20:31.048
mmm.
That's good.

341
00:20:31.050 --> 00:20:32.916
...is that
you and I both know

342
00:20:32.918 --> 00:20:35.786
that I've been burned
by you Winchesters before.

343
00:20:35.788 --> 00:20:37.387
yet you still call.

344
00:20:37.389 --> 00:20:40.524
Yeah. I know.
but not this time. okay?

345
00:20:40.526 --> 00:20:45.963
No games.
no second thoughts.

346
00:20:45.965 --> 00:20:47.864
I know you know
what this is.

347
00:20:48.733 --> 00:20:50.233
I know you know
what it can do.

348
00:20:50.235 --> 00:20:51.802
I've tried
to fight it.

349
00:20:51.804 --> 00:20:55.172
I've tried
to beat it on my own.

350
00:20:55.174 --> 00:20:56.373
And I-I can't.

351
00:20:56.375 --> 00:21:01.578
I got no moves left --
except you.

352
00:21:01.580 --> 00:21:05.015
Well. I never thought
I'd see the day.

353
00:21:05.017 --> 00:21:07.084
My goodness.

354
00:21:07.086 --> 00:21:10.587
Dean Winchester
has tipped over his king.

355
00:21:12.156 --> 00:21:15.392
But I won't kill you.
Dean.

356
00:21:16.260 --> 00:21:18.128
You're death.

357
00:21:18.131 --> 00:21:21.332
And that Mark on your arm
is the First Curse.

358
00:21:21.333 --> 00:21:23.066
Nothing can kill you.

359
00:21:23.068 --> 00:21:25.969
Okay. well. forget killing me.
Can you get rid of it?

360
00:21:25.971 --> 00:21:28.038
I could.

361
00:21:28.040 --> 00:21:30.273
But...

362
00:21:30.275 --> 00:21:32.642
Creatio ex nihilo --

363
00:21:32.645 --> 00:21:35.380
God created the earth
out of nothing --

364
00:21:35.381 --> 00:21:39.249
or so your Sunday-school teacher
would have you believe.

365
00:21:39.251 --> 00:21:41.151
What. so
Genesis is a lie. eh?

366
00:21:41.153 --> 00:21:42.552
Shocker.

367
00:21:44.155 --> 00:21:45.522
Before there was light.

368
00:21:45.525 --> 00:21:48.026
before there was God
and the archangels.

369
00:21:48.027 --> 00:21:50.193
there wasn't nothing.

370
00:21:50.195 --> 00:21:52.829
There was the Darkness.

371
00:21:52.831 --> 00:21:55.132
a horribly destructive.
amoral force

372
00:21:55.135 --> 00:21:58.002
that was beaten back
by God and his archangels

373
00:21:58.003 --> 00:22:00.037
in a terrible war.

374
00:22:00.040 --> 00:22:03.941
God locked the Darkness away
where it could do no harm.

375
00:22:03.943 --> 00:22:10.048
and he created a Mark that would
serve as both lock and key.

376
00:22:10.049 --> 00:22:14.651
which he entrusted to his
most valued Lieutenant. Lucifer.

377
00:22:14.654 --> 00:22:18.423
But the Mark began
to assert its own will.

378
00:22:18.424 --> 00:22:22.659
revealed itself as a curse.
and began to corrupt.

379
00:22:22.661 --> 00:22:25.495
Lucifer
became jealous of man.

380
00:22:25.498 --> 00:22:28.533
God banished Lucifer
to Hell.

381
00:22:28.535 --> 00:22:31.736
Lucifer passed the Mark
to Cain.

382
00:22:31.738 --> 00:22:34.639
who passed the Mark
to you.

383
00:22:34.640 --> 00:22:39.142
the proverbial
finger in the dike.

384
00:22:41.012 --> 00:22:44.848
Well. that is just
fan-friggin-tastic. isn't it?

385
00:22:44.851 --> 00:22:47.585
So I could
remove the Mark.

386
00:22:47.586 --> 00:22:51.421
but only if
you will share it with another

387
00:22:51.423 --> 00:22:55.125
to ensure
that the lock remains unbroken

388
00:22:55.127 --> 00:22:59.096
and the Darkness
remains banned.

389
00:22:59.098 --> 00:23:03.133
I'm not doing that...

390
00:23:03.135 --> 00:23:06.736
not to anyone.

391
00:23:06.738 --> 00:23:09.906
What if I told you I could
relocate you somewhere far away.

392
00:23:09.908 --> 00:23:11.875
not even
on this earth.

393
00:23:11.877 --> 00:23:14.377
where you
would still be alive.

394
00:23:14.379 --> 00:23:18.115
but no longer a danger
to yourself or to others?

395
00:23:26.391 --> 00:23:27.591
Dean.

396
00:23:27.593 --> 00:23:29.426
I gave it a shot.
Sammy.

397
00:23:29.428 --> 00:23:32.062
Listen to me --
whatever you're doing.

398
00:23:32.064 --> 00:23:34.331
whatever you've done.
please...

399
00:23:34.333 --> 00:23:38.468
Hell. I even worked a case.

400
00:23:38.470 --> 00:23:41.271
I gave everything I had
to beat this thing down.

401
00:23:41.273 --> 00:23:44.174
I saw. I saw Rudy.

402
00:23:44.176 --> 00:23:46.143
Well. then. you saw
what I did.

403
00:23:46.145 --> 00:23:47.711
No. that wasn't you.

404
00:23:47.713 --> 00:23:50.213
Sure as hell
felt like me.

405
00:23:52.517 --> 00:23:54.417
Brother. I'm done.

406
00:23:54.419 --> 00:23:56.753
No. No. you're not.
Dean.

407
00:23:56.755 --> 00:23:59.823
Grab a pen.
It's time to say goodbye.

408
00:23:59.825 --> 00:24:03.293
Get you a refill.
Jimmy.

409
00:24:11.702 --> 00:24:13.470
Fancy a story?

410
00:24:13.472 --> 00:24:14.738
You?

411
00:24:14.740 --> 00:24:16.806
What did you do?

412
00:24:23.714 --> 00:24:25.982
A long. long time ago.

413
00:24:25.984 --> 00:24:29.719
there once lived
an evil bitch -- sorry. witch --

414
00:24:29.721 --> 00:24:32.222
who was forced to flee her home
and her only son

415
00:24:32.224 --> 00:24:35.625
because she was.
well. horrible.

416
00:24:35.627 --> 00:24:37.527
Starving and homeless.

417
00:24:37.529 --> 00:24:40.130
she threw herself upon the mercy
of a peasant Polish family

418
00:24:40.132 --> 00:24:42.666
who took her in.
fed her.

419
00:24:42.668 --> 00:24:44.634
and nursed her
back to full strength.

420
00:24:44.636 --> 00:24:46.870
This was a kindness
she had never known.

421
00:24:46.872 --> 00:24:50.307
She was particularly taken
by their 8-year-old son

422
00:24:50.309 --> 00:24:54.344
who. apparently.
she grew to love.

423
00:24:54.346 --> 00:24:55.779
Mm.

424
00:24:57.815 --> 00:24:59.382
How do you know
all this?

425
00:24:59.384 --> 00:25:01.985
A hamster told me.

426
00:25:03.821 --> 00:25:05.188
Tragically...

427
00:25:06.490 --> 00:25:10.060
...the boy was terminally ill
and soon to die.

428
00:25:10.062 --> 00:25:11.861
But before
the witch departed.

429
00:25:11.863 --> 00:25:13.430
she gave the boy
and his family

430
00:25:13.432 --> 00:25:16.333
the only thanks
that made sense.

431
00:25:16.335 --> 00:25:18.401
She cured the boy
with one spell

432
00:25:18.403 --> 00:25:21.838
and cast another that would take
root once he was full-grown.

433
00:25:21.840 --> 00:25:25.175
That lying. manipulative
whore mother of mine

434
00:25:25.177 --> 00:25:28.178
gave you immortality.
didn't she...Oskar?

435
00:25:47.733 --> 00:25:48.999
Hey.

436
00:25:49.001 --> 00:25:50.400
Sam.

437
00:25:53.304 --> 00:25:54.771
What is this?

438
00:25:54.773 --> 00:25:56.906
We need to talk.

439
00:25:56.908 --> 00:25:59.809
Whatever you are thinking
of doing. don't.

440
00:25:59.811 --> 00:26:02.445
There is another way.

441
00:26:02.447 --> 00:26:05.448
You don't need to go with him.
You don't need to die!

442
00:26:05.450 --> 00:26:08.285
Funny you say that.

443
00:26:08.287 --> 00:26:10.754
Truth is. when I left.

444
00:26:10.756 --> 00:26:13.256
I thought the only way out
<i>was</i> my death.

445
00:26:14.292 --> 00:26:16.126
Well. I was wrong. Sam.

446
00:26:16.128 --> 00:26:19.362
It's yours.

447
00:26:28.069 --> 00:26:30.705
What?
He's gonna...

448
00:26:30.706 --> 00:26:32.372
Gonna send you
into outer space?

449
00:26:32.374 --> 00:26:33.974
No. well. he didn't
say outer space.

450
00:26:33.976 --> 00:26:35.175
This is madness.
Dean!

451
00:26:35.177 --> 00:26:36.543
Far from it.
I'm afraid.

452
00:26:36.545 --> 00:26:38.612
No one's asking you.
Hear him out!

453
00:26:38.614 --> 00:26:40.747
Our conundrum
is simple. Sam.

454
00:26:40.749 --> 00:26:42.983
Your brother
cannot be killed.

455
00:26:42.986 --> 00:26:45.219
and the Mark
cannot be destroyed.

456
00:26:45.220 --> 00:26:47.854
not without inciting
a far greater evil

457
00:26:47.856 --> 00:26:50.190
than any of us
have ever known.

458
00:26:50.192 --> 00:26:51.324
What evil?

459
00:26:51.326 --> 00:26:52.326
The Darkness.

460
00:26:52.327 --> 00:26:53.360
What the hell is that?

461
00:26:53.362 --> 00:26:54.561
Well.
what does it sound like?

462
00:26:54.563 --> 00:26:56.129
Does it sound
like a good thing?

463
00:26:57.465 --> 00:27:01.535
Even if I remove Dean
from the playing field.

464
00:27:01.537 --> 00:27:05.605
we're still left with you.
loyal. dogged Sam.

465
00:27:05.607 --> 00:27:06.907
who I suspect
will never rest

466
00:27:06.909 --> 00:27:09.709
until he sets his brother
free --

467
00:27:09.712 --> 00:27:14.248
will never rest until
his brother is free of the Mark.

468
00:27:14.249 --> 00:27:16.683
which simply
cannot happen.

469
00:27:16.685 --> 00:27:20.754
lest the Darkness
be set free.

470
00:27:22.523 --> 00:27:25.892
Then there was that time
you stood me up.

471
00:27:31.432 --> 00:27:33.033
You traded my life.

472
00:27:33.035 --> 00:27:36.269
I'm willing to live
with this thing forever.

473
00:27:36.271 --> 00:27:38.705
as long as I know
that I and it

474
00:27:38.707 --> 00:27:40.574
will never hurt
another living thing.

475
00:27:40.576 --> 00:27:42.609
This isn't you.

476
00:27:42.611 --> 00:27:45.679
This doesn't make any sense.

477
00:27:45.681 --> 00:27:47.681
No.
it makes perfect sense

478
00:27:47.683 --> 00:27:50.483
if you stop thinking about
yourself for one damn minute!

479
00:27:50.485 --> 00:27:53.520
It's for the greater good.

480
00:27:53.522 --> 00:27:55.255
Once you consider that.

481
00:27:55.257 --> 00:27:58.391
this makes
all the sense in the world.

482
00:28:02.196 --> 00:28:05.498
Why the long faces?

483
00:28:06.901 --> 00:28:09.002
Oh. Let me guess.

484
00:28:09.004 --> 00:28:12.372
Mother showed you
her "mustn't touch it" again.

485
00:28:12.374 --> 00:28:14.107
Do you have
the ingredients?

486
00:28:19.146 --> 00:28:21.047
The Quince cost me
a major I.O.U.

487
00:28:21.049 --> 00:28:23.250
with
a Palestinian warlock.

488
00:28:23.252 --> 00:28:25.151
The gold from the calf --

489
00:28:25.153 --> 00:28:27.153
well. let's just say
I'll be hanged

490
00:28:27.155 --> 00:28:29.089
under certain
sexual-deviancy laws

491
00:28:29.091 --> 00:28:31.691
if I ever show my face
in Jordan again.

492
00:28:31.693 --> 00:28:33.360
And the third?

493
00:28:33.362 --> 00:28:35.128
Ah. yes.

494
00:28:37.498 --> 00:28:40.700
All my long life.
I wondered what I'd done

495
00:28:40.702 --> 00:28:43.336
to deserve a mother
who refused to show love.

496
00:28:47.041 --> 00:28:49.309
I pained over it.

497
00:28:49.311 --> 00:28:53.280
I built my bloody kingdom
on top of it.

498
00:28:53.282 --> 00:28:56.683
Then one day.
epiphany struck.

499
00:28:56.685 --> 00:29:01.121
My mother was incapable
of loving anything.

500
00:29:01.123 --> 00:29:05.258
For the first time
in hundreds of years.

501
00:29:05.260 --> 00:29:06.626
I felt free.

502
00:29:06.628 --> 00:29:09.429
And then you showed up
in my dungeon.

503
00:29:09.431 --> 00:29:11.498
we communed.

504
00:29:11.500 --> 00:29:16.102
and I began to realize
you weren't incapable of love.

505
00:29:17.605 --> 00:29:19.506
You're incapable
of loving <i>me.</i>

506
00:29:19.508 --> 00:29:22.809
Goodness. Fergus. save it
for the stage. why don't you?

507
00:29:22.811 --> 00:29:24.377
I mean.
fabulous speech.

508
00:29:24.379 --> 00:29:27.013
but you put yourself
on far too high a pedestal.

509
00:29:27.015 --> 00:29:31.952
The fact remains I do not.
will not.

510
00:29:31.954 --> 00:29:34.988
and have not
loved anything ever.

511
00:29:56.411 --> 00:29:58.178
You were saying?

512
00:29:58.180 --> 00:29:59.879
Remember when
we were in that church.

513
00:29:59.881 --> 00:30:01.348
making Crowley human.

514
00:30:01.350 --> 00:30:03.249
about to close
the Gates of Hell?

515
00:30:03.251 --> 00:30:04.684
Well.
you sure as hell

516
00:30:04.686 --> 00:30:07.487
were ready to die
for the greater good then.

517
00:30:07.489 --> 00:30:09.889
Yeah. and. Dean.
you pulled me back.

518
00:30:09.891 --> 00:30:11.891
And I was wrong.

519
00:30:11.893 --> 00:30:13.493
You were right. Sam.

520
00:30:13.495 --> 00:30:16.997
You knew that this world would
be better without us in it.

521
00:30:16.999 --> 00:30:18.298
No. no. no.
wait a second.

522
00:30:18.300 --> 00:30:19.966
You're twisting my words here.
Dean.

523
00:30:19.968 --> 00:30:22.769
Why? Because we --
we track evil and kill it?

524
00:30:22.771 --> 00:30:25.005
The family business?
Is that it?

525
00:30:25.007 --> 00:30:28.141
Look at the tape. Sam.

526
00:30:28.143 --> 00:30:30.510
Evil tracks <i>us.</i>

527
00:30:30.512 --> 00:30:32.912
And it nukes everything
in our vicinity --

528
00:30:32.914 --> 00:30:34.581
our family.
our friends.

529
00:30:34.583 --> 00:30:37.350
It's time we put a proper name
to what we really are

530
00:30:37.352 --> 00:30:40.487
and we deal with it.

531
00:30:40.489 --> 00:30:41.788
Wait a second.

532
00:30:41.790 --> 00:30:45.492
We are <i>not</i> evil.

533
00:30:45.494 --> 00:30:46.893
Listen...

534
00:30:46.895 --> 00:30:50.663
We're far from perfect.
but we are good.

535
00:30:52.066 --> 00:30:55.001
That thing on your arm
is evil.

536
00:30:55.003 --> 00:30:58.271
but not you. not me.

537
00:30:58.273 --> 00:31:00.974
I let Rudy die.

538
00:31:02.843 --> 00:31:04.911
How was that not evil?

539
00:31:04.913 --> 00:31:07.213
I know
what I am. Sam.

540
00:31:07.215 --> 00:31:10.283
But who were you
when you --

541
00:31:10.285 --> 00:31:14.621
when you drove that man
to sell his soul...

542
00:31:14.623 --> 00:31:17.323
Or when
you bullied Charlie

543
00:31:17.325 --> 00:31:20.126
into
getting herself killed?

544
00:31:20.128 --> 00:31:21.861
And to what end?

545
00:31:21.863 --> 00:31:23.897
A-a good end?

546
00:31:23.899 --> 00:31:25.465
A just end?

547
00:31:25.468 --> 00:31:28.769
To remove the Mark no matter
what the consequences?

548
00:31:28.770 --> 00:31:30.637
Sam.
how is that not evil?

549
00:31:30.639 --> 00:31:33.473
I have this thing
on my arm.

550
00:31:33.475 --> 00:31:37.577
and you're willing to let
the Darkness into the world.

551
00:31:37.579 --> 00:31:39.612
You were also willing
to summon death

552
00:31:39.614 --> 00:31:44.951
to make sure you could
never do any more harm.

553
00:31:44.953 --> 00:31:47.153
You summoned me
because you knew

554
00:31:47.155 --> 00:31:50.623
I would do anything
to protect you.

555
00:31:50.625 --> 00:31:52.959
That's not evil.
Dean.

556
00:31:52.961 --> 00:31:55.428
That's not
an evil man.

557
00:31:55.430 --> 00:31:59.032
That is a good man
crying to be heard.

558
00:31:59.034 --> 00:32:03.803
searching for...
some other way.

559
00:32:03.805 --> 00:32:05.939
No. there is
no other way. Sam.

560
00:32:05.941 --> 00:32:08.441
I'm sorry.

561
00:32:15.716 --> 00:32:17.517
Good.

562
00:32:17.519 --> 00:32:18.885
Good.

563
00:32:21.122 --> 00:32:22.388
Fight.

564
00:32:22.923 --> 00:32:27.127
This is ridiculous.

565
00:32:27.129 --> 00:32:29.929
Do you love this man?
Rowena. is it true?

566
00:32:29.931 --> 00:32:31.831
'Course it's true.

567
00:32:31.833 --> 00:32:33.366
Say hello. Oskar.

568
00:32:36.804 --> 00:32:38.104
Rowena.

569
00:32:38.106 --> 00:32:40.640
Even for you. Fergus.

570
00:32:40.642 --> 00:32:42.475
this is a new low --

571
00:32:42.477 --> 00:32:46.980
a cruel. shameful.
disgusting low.

572
00:32:46.982 --> 00:32:50.550
It's only cruel if you
actually go through with it.

573
00:32:50.552 --> 00:32:52.652
Though...

574
00:32:54.188 --> 00:32:56.689
...who's the cruel one then?

575
00:33:10.938 --> 00:33:12.605
Aah! Aah!

576
00:33:20.481 --> 00:33:22.282
Ohh!

577
00:33:25.119 --> 00:33:27.053
Okay.

578
00:33:27.055 --> 00:33:29.923
That's enough.
Hey. that's enough.

579
00:33:37.765 --> 00:33:44.404
You'll never. ever
hear me say

580
00:33:44.406 --> 00:33:51.544
that you -- the real you --
is anything but good.

581
00:34:00.921 --> 00:34:03.022
But you're right.

582
00:34:03.024 --> 00:34:09.729
Before you hurt...
anyone else.

583
00:34:09.731 --> 00:34:15.802
you have to be stopped
at any cost.

584
00:34:15.804 --> 00:34:19.339
I understand.

585
00:34:24.246 --> 00:34:26.179
Do it.

586
00:34:29.516 --> 00:34:32.552
Please.

587
00:34:35.022 --> 00:34:37.557
Do me the honor.

588
00:34:59.581 --> 00:35:02.682
Close your eyes.

589
00:35:07.855 --> 00:35:12.091
Sammy.
close your eyes.

590
00:35:15.963 --> 00:35:19.565
Wait.

591
00:35:19.567 --> 00:35:21.367
Take these.

592
00:35:21.369 --> 00:35:22.735
And one day.

593
00:35:22.737 --> 00:35:26.372
when you
find your way back...

594
00:35:26.374 --> 00:35:29.509
Let these
be your guide.

595
00:35:29.511 --> 00:35:32.312
And they can
help you remember

596
00:35:32.314 --> 00:35:34.914
what it was
to be good...

597
00:35:37.117 --> 00:35:39.686
...what it was to love.

598
00:35:56.837 --> 00:36:00.673
It's for family
you must proceed. Dean.

599
00:36:00.675 --> 00:36:03.710
To be what you are.
to become what you've become

600
00:36:03.712 --> 00:36:07.947
is a stain
on their memory.

601
00:36:07.949 --> 00:36:09.749
Do it.

602
00:36:12.019 --> 00:36:14.253
Or I will.

603
00:36:28.702 --> 00:36:30.937
Forgive me.

604
00:37:05.786 --> 00:37:08.020
You've grown so big.

605
00:37:08.022 --> 00:37:12.258
Not too big to give your old
auntie Rowena a hug I hope.

606
00:37:12.260 --> 00:37:14.393
Hope
I haven't hurt you.

607
00:37:14.395 --> 00:37:18.464
Don't
think about that one moment.

608
00:37:18.466 --> 00:37:22.602
Everything's fine.
Oskar.

609
00:37:22.604 --> 00:37:24.937
Everything's fine.

610
00:37:24.939 --> 00:37:28.875
Nobody's
hurting anybody.

611
00:37:28.877 --> 00:37:32.278
Goodbye.
my sweet wee boy.

612
00:37:48.862 --> 00:37:50.763
<i>Ab manu dei...</i>

613
00:37:50.765 --> 00:37:53.666
<i>Ab manu hominis.</i>

614
00:37:56.237 --> 00:37:57.570
You okay?

615
00:37:57.572 --> 00:38:01.207
I'll live.

616
00:38:02.576 --> 00:38:03.876
You?

617
00:38:03.878 --> 00:38:05.811
Fantastic.

618
00:38:05.813 --> 00:38:08.547
I think
I just killed death.

619
00:38:08.549 --> 00:38:13.019
<i>Ab cruore cordis</i>
<i>Mei adfusuro in aeternum.</i>

620
00:38:13.021 --> 00:38:18.758
<i>Tolle maledictionem</i>
<i>tuam ab hoc viro.</i>

621
00:38:33.840 --> 00:38:35.274
That sound right
to you?

622
00:38:39.681 --> 00:38:42.114
Aah!

623
00:38:58.832 --> 00:39:00.967
Ah.

624
00:39:04.005 --> 00:39:05.471
<i>Manete!</i>

625
00:39:05.473 --> 00:39:07.573
What is this?

626
00:39:09.543 --> 00:39:10.876
This is impossible.

627
00:39:10.878 --> 00:39:13.012
You're not
powerful enough.

628
00:39:13.014 --> 00:39:14.547
To what?

629
00:39:14.549 --> 00:39:17.183
Control the likes of a
bored king and a wayward angel?

630
00:39:18.586 --> 00:39:20.653
<i>Impetus bestiarum.</i>

631
00:39:22.123 --> 00:39:25.191
I'm afraid. Fergus.
that in all your long life.

632
00:39:25.193 --> 00:39:28.894
you've never seen what a real
witch can do with real magic.

633
00:39:28.896 --> 00:39:31.430
I'm
terrifically pleased

634
00:39:31.432 --> 00:39:34.767
it's the last thing
you'll ever see.

635
00:39:34.769 --> 00:39:38.204
<i>Dele malum hoc.</i>

636
00:39:40.375 --> 00:39:41.907
Castiel.

637
00:39:41.909 --> 00:39:43.009
Don't.

638
00:39:44.278 --> 00:39:45.911
Do not.

639
00:39:45.913 --> 00:39:48.314
Don't!

640
00:39:48.849 --> 00:39:49.849
Please!

641
00:39:52.519 --> 00:39:54.086
This is good.

642
00:39:54.088 --> 00:39:55.454
Dean. this is good.

643
00:39:55.457 --> 00:39:57.224
The -- the Mark
is off your arm.

644
00:39:57.225 --> 00:40:00.993
Nothing crazy happened.
You get your baby back.

645
00:40:00.995 --> 00:40:03.129
Yeah.

646
00:40:03.131 --> 00:40:05.531
I'm sure everything's
perfectly fine.

647
00:40:09.903 --> 00:40:11.704
What?

648
00:40:26.219 --> 00:40:28.754
What did death
call this?

649
00:40:28.756 --> 00:40:30.556
The Darkness.

650
00:40:59.219 --> 00:41:00.286
Get in the car.
Yeah.

651
00:41:00.288 --> 00:41:01.420
Let's go. let's go!

652
00:41:22.042 --> 00:41:23.242
Dean.

653
00:41:44.965 --> 00:41:46.499
Dean!

654
00:41:58.856 --> 00:42:05.356
== sync. corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>
